Final note from Wisconsin Supreme Court debate/forum hosted today by Milwaukee Bar Association:

@JudgeNeubauer said the phrase "fair, impartial and independent" 14 times, or roughly once every four minutes or so

Also, live stream viewership hovered around 10 for the entire hour

Closing remarks:

@JudgeNeubauer cites her 30-plus years' experience in the law, including past 11 on court of appeals

She also notes that 98 percent of endorsing judges have picked her over @judgehagedorn

Asked about biggest challenge is facing Wisconsin courts:

@JudgeNeubauer says every courthouse is struggling, largely due to drug crisis, but also getting needed health and human services 

@judgehagedorn says biggest challenge is "to not let our court become politicized"

.@JudgeNeubauer says if elected she will not go to political events, meetings

She says she's doing it as a candidate, but hasn't as an appeals court judge

@judgehagedorn says he won't go to partisan events if elected, and he's only done it as a candidate

Question about position on 2nd amendment (guns) and school choice

@judgehagedorn says he will uphold constitutional right to bear arms

@NRA has endorsed Hagedorn in the race

@JudgeNeubauer declines to comment on the issues because they may come to court

@judgehagedorn:

"There's nothing wrong, there's nothing inconsistent with living out your faith in your own life and being a judge."

He is an evangelical Christian, says his personal beliefs don't affect his interpretation of the law

.@JudgeNeubauer asked how she would respond to recuse from case involving unions that have spent money to support her campaign does not say what she would do.

@judgehagedorn
points out that she failed to answer the question

O'Rourke officially launched his Democratic bid for president last week in neighboring Iowa

@realDonaldTrump carried Wisconsin in 2016 by fewer than 23,000 votes, the first Republican to win since 1984

Wisconsin has 10 electoral votes

Republican committee members are divided over whether to confirm Dawn Crim, @GovEvers pick to lead @WI_DSPS 

@SenatorDevin says he supports Crim

@SenDaveCraig says he needs to think about it

Chairman @SenatorKapenga says he has questions, won't immediately schedule a vote
